1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,571
One, get a balanced view of the other fellow.

2
00:00:03,841 --> 00:00:07,411
Keep these two points in mind when dealing with people.

3
00:00:07,601 --> 00:00:10,530
First, the other fellow is important.

4
00:00:10,721 --> 00:00:12,931
Emphatically, he is important.

5
00:00:13,041 --> 00:00:14,770
Every human being is.

6
00:00:15,041 --> 00:00:16,770
But remember this also.

7
00:00:17,041 --> 00:00:18,770
You are important too.

8
00:00:19,041 --> 00:00:29,010
So when you meet another person, make it a policy to think, we're just two important people sitting down to discuss something of mutual interest and benefit.

9
00:00:29,601 --> 00:00:38,691
A couple of months ago, a business executive phoned to tell me he had just employed a young man whom I had recommended to him shortly before.

10
00:00:39,041 --> 00:00:43,010
Do you know what really sold me on that fellow, asked my friend.

11
00:00:43,361 --> 00:00:44,611
What, I asked.

12
00:00:45,281 --> 00:00:47,811
Well, it was the way he handled himself.

13
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:51,891
Most job applicants, when they walk in here, are half scared.

14
00:00:52,081 --> 00:00:55,250
They give me all the answers they think I want to hear.

15
00:00:55,441 --> 00:00:59,010
In a way, most job applicants are a little like beggars.

16
00:00:59,121 --> 00:01:02,211
They'll accept anything, and they aren't particular.

17
00:01:02,721 --> 00:01:05,250
But G handled himself differently.

18
00:01:05,361 --> 00:01:10,290
He respected me, but what's just as important, he respects himself.

19
00:01:10,561 --> 00:01:14,851
What's more, he asked me as many questions as I asked him.

20
00:01:14,961 --> 00:01:16,211
He's no mouse.

21
00:01:16,321 --> 00:01:19,571
He's a real man, and he's going to do all right.

22
00:01:20,480 --> 00:01:25,250
This mutually important attitude helps you keep the situation balanced.

